title: Casey Anthony joins Donald Trump protests in Palm Beach | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad Casey Anthony joins protest of President Donald Trump outside Mar-a-Lago in Palm Beach over the weekend Casey Anthony was one of the 3,000 protesters who marched in a rally outside Mar-a-Lago on Saturday night The protest was held while President Donald Trump and the First Lady were at their Florida estate for the annual Red Cross Ball Casey, 30, was seen talking to fellow protesters while smiling and waving in video from the event In another video she spoke with a group of men and after laughing at one of them could be seen taking her phone out and typing something into the device Casey declined a request to be interviewed on camera, but said she is against President Trump's policies Her night of protesting came almost six years after she was found not guilty of killing her daughter Caylee in 2011 Published: 20:01 GMT, 6 February 2017 | Updated: 02:25 GMT, 7 February 2017 706 shares
